# {{ project_name }}

A [dropmcp](https://github.com/agoda-com/dropmcp) skills & prompts MCP server.

## Layout

```
skills/          # SKILL.md folders → MCP tools
prompts/         # PROMPT.md folders → MCP prompts
INSTRUCTIONS.md  # Server instructions ({% raw %}{{INSTRUCTION_SUMMARIES}}{% endraw %} placeholders)
server.py        # One-liner entrypoint
requirements.txt # Pinned dropmcp dependency
```

## Local development

Install dependencies (pins `dropmcp=={{ dropmcp_version }}`):

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Validate content:

```bash
dropmcp validate
```

Run over stdio (Cursor / Claude Desktop):

```bash
python server.py
```

Run over HTTP (hosted / catalog UI at `/catalog`):

```bash
DROPMCP_TRANSPORT=http DROPMCP_PORT=8080 python server.py
```

Or use the CLI:

```bash
dropmcp serve --skills skills --prompts prompts
dropmcp serve --skills skills --prompts prompts --transport http --port 8080
```

## Docker

```bash
docker build -t {{ project_slug }} .
docker run --rm -p 8080:8080 {{ project_slug }}
```

Open http://localhost:8080/catalog to browse skills and prompts.

